===Etymology===
ipu > iɸu > *iwu > iu. Medial /h/ regularly changed from [p] > [ɸ] > [w]. Japanese never distinguished between /wu/ and /u/, so it automatically becomes [u]. The /w/ only surfaces in negative form: iwanai, where the phoneme /wa/ exists. Surface forms /iwimasu/ and /iwemasu/ automatically become [iimasu] and [iemasu] since Japanese no longer distinguishes /wi, we/ from /i, e/. Possibly related to Korean [[입]] (ip) “mouth”.

